===Etymology===
Probably Sino-Tibetan; compare {{cog|bo|དབྱི|t=lynx}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Schuessler also sees possible cognacy with ''pi'' ~ ''byi'' in {{cog|bo|པི་ཤི}} and {{m|bo|བྱི་ལ}}, though ''pi'' ~ ''byi'' might be derived from {{w|Indo-Aryan languages|Indic}} (cf. {{cog|hi|बिल्ला}} < {{cog|sa| बिडाल}}; see the Sanskrit word for ultimate non-Indic etymology); even so, ''pi'' ~ ''byi'' is still possibly native Tibetan if {{m|bo|པི་ཤི}}'s ''shi'' was from earlier *''zhi'' and cognate with {{och-l|狸}}, see there for more ([[ibid.]]).

